Authors: 1,Stephen,King,1947-09-21,NULL,American,Known for his horror, supernatural fiction, suspense, crime, and fantasy novels.

2,Jane,Austen,1775-12-16,1817-07-18,British,An English novelist known primarily for her six major novels, which interpret, critique, and comment upon the British landed gentry at the end of the 18th century.

3,George,Orwell,1903-06-25,1950-01-21,British,An English novelist, essayist, journalist, and critic whose work is characterised by lucid prose, biting social criticism, opposition to totalitarianism, and outspoken support of democratic socialism.

4,Agatha,Christie,1890-09-15,1976-01-12,British,An English writer known for her 66 detective novels and 14 short story collections, particularly those featuring fictional detectives Hercule Poirot and Miss Marple.
5,J.K.,Rowling,1965-07-31,NULL,British,A British author, philanthropist, film producer, and screenwriter, best known for writing the Harry Potter fantasy series.
6,Ernest,Hemingway,1899-07-21,1961-07-02,American,An American novelist, short-story writer, and journalist. His economical and understated style had a strong influence on 20th-century fiction.

7,Virginia,Woolf,1882-01-25,1941-03-28,British,An English writer, considered one of the most important modernist 20th-century authors and a pioneer in the use of stream of consciousness as a narrative device.
8,Gabriel Garcia,Marquez,1927-03-06,2014-04-17,Colombian,A Colombian novelist, short-story writer, screenwriter, and journalist, known for his magical realism.
9,Toni,Morrison,1931-02-18,2019-08-05,American,An American novelist, essayist, book editor, and college professor. Her first novel, The Bluest Eye, was published in 1970.

10,Haruki,Murakami,1949-01-12,NULL,Japanese,A Japanese writer. His books and stories have been bestsellers in Japan and internationally, with his work translated into 50 languages and selling millions of copies outside Japan.

11,Leo,Tolstoy,1828-09-09,1910-11-20,Russian,A Russian writer who is regarded as one of the greatest authors of all time. He received nominations for the Nobel Prize in Literature every year from 1902 to 1906.
12,Mary,Shelley,1797-08-30,1851-02-01,British,An English novelist who wrote the Gothic novel Frankenstein; or, The Modern Prometheus (1818).
13,F. Scott,Fitzgerald,1896-09-24,1940-12-21,American,An American novelist, essayist, short story writer, and screenwriter. He is best known for his novels depicting the Jazz Age.

14,Charles,Dickens,1812-02-07,1870-06-09,British,An English writer and social critic. He created some of the world's best-known fictional characters and is regarded by many as the greatest novelist of the Victorian era.
15,Herman,Melville,1819-08-01,1891-09-28,American,An American novelist, short story writer, and poet of the American Renaissance period. Among his best-known works are Moby Dick and Billy Budd.
16,Emily,BrontÃ«,1818-07-30,1848-12-19,British,An English novelist and poet who is best known for her only novel, Wuthering Heights, a classic of English literature.
17,Mark,Twain,1835-11-30,1910-04-21,American,An American writer, humorist, entrepreneur, publisher, and lecturer. He was lauded as the 'greatest American humorist of his age'.
18,Victor,Hugo,1802-02-26,1885-05-22,French,A French poet, novelist, and dramatist of the Romantic movement. He is considered one of the greatest and best-known French writers.
19,Albert,Camus,1913-11-07,1960-01-04,French,A French philosopher, author, and journalist. He was awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature at the age of 44 in 1957.
20,Franz,Kafka,1883-07-03,1924-06-03,Czech,A German-speaking Bohemian novelist and short-story writer, widely regarded as one of the major figures of 20th-century literature.

21,Chinua,Achebe,1930-11-16,2013-03-21,Nigerian,A Nigerian novelist, poet, professor, and literary critic. His first novel Things Fall Apart (1958) is the most widely read book in modern African literature.

22,Isabel,Allende,1942-08-02,NULL,Chilean,A Chilean writer. Allende, whose works sometimes contain aspects of 'magical realism', is known for her novels such as The House of the Spirits and City of the Beasts.
23,Kazuo,Ishiguro,1954-11-08,NULL,British,A British novelist, screenwriter, and short-story writer. He was born in Nagasaki, Japan, and moved to England in 1960.
24,Margaret,Atwood,1939-11-18,NULL,Canadian,A Canadian poet, novelist, literary critic, essayist, inventor, teacher, and environmental activist. She has won numerous awards for her work.
25,Neil,Gaiman,1960-11-10,NULL,British,An English author of short fiction, novels, comic books, graphic novels, non-fiction, audio theatre, and films.
26,Ursula K.,Le Guin,1929-10-21,2018-01-22,American,An American author best known for her works of fantasy and science fiction. She wrote more than 20 novels and over 100 short stories.
27,Philip K.,Dick,1928-12-16,1982-03-02,American,An American science fiction writer. He wrote 44 novels and about 121 short stories, most of which appeared in science fiction magazines.

28,Octavia E.,Butler,1947-06-22,2006-02-24,American,An American science fiction writer. A multiple recipient of both the Hugo and Nebula awards, she was the first science fiction writer to receive a MacArthur Fellowship.
29,J.R.R.,Tolkien,1892-01-03,1973-09-02,British,An English writer, poet, philologist, and academic, best known as the author of the high fantasy works The Hobbit and The Lord of the Rings.
30,C.S.,Lewis,1898-11-29,1963-11-22,British,A British writer and lay theologian. He held academic positions in English literature at both Oxford and Cambridge Universities.
31,Daphne du,Maurier,1907-05-13,1989-04-19,British,An English author and playwright. Many of her works have been adapted into films, including Rebecca, Jamaica Inn, and The Birds.
32,Kurt,Vonnegut,1922-11-11,2007-04-11,American,An American writer. In a career spanning over 50 years, he published 14 novels, three short story collections, five plays, and five non-fiction works.
33,Aldous,Huxley,1894-07-26,1963-11-22,British,An English writer and philosopher. He wrote nearly 50 books, including novels, essays, and poems.
34,Ray,Bradbury,1920-08-22,2012-06-05,American,An American author and screenwriter. He worked in a variety of genres, including fantasy, science fiction, horror, and mystery fiction.
35,Arthur C.,Clarke,1917-12-16,2008-03-19,British,A British science fiction writer, science writer, futurist, inventor, undersea explorer, and television series host.
36,Isaac,Asimov,1920-01-02,1992-04-06,American,An American writer and professor of biochemistry at Boston University. He was known for his works of science fiction and popular science.
37,Frank,Herbert,1920-10-08,1986-02-11,American,An American science fiction author best known for the 1965 novel Dune and its five sequels.
38,William,Gibson,1948-03-17,NULL,American,An American-Canadian speculative fiction writer and essayist widely credited with pioneering the science fiction subgenre of cyberpunk.
39,George R.R.,Martin,1948-09-20,NULL,American,An American novelist and short story writer in the fantasy, horror, and science fiction genres, a screenwriter, and television producer.
40,Brandon,Sanderson,1975-12-19,NULL,American,An American fantasy and science fiction writer. He is best known for the Cosmere fictional universe, in which most of his fantasy novels are set.
41,Terry,Pratchett,1948-04-28,2015-03-12,British,An English humorist, satirist, and author of fantasy novels, especially his Discworld series.
42,Douglas,Adams,1952-03-11,2001-05-11,British,An English author, satirist, and comic radio dramatist. He is best known for The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy.
43,Suzanne,Collins,1962-08-10,NULL,American,An American author. She is best known for The Hunger Games series.
44,Veronica,Roth,1988-08-19,NULL,American,An American novelist and short story writer, known for her Divergent trilogy.
45,John,Green,1977-08-24,NULL,American,An American author and YouTube content creator. He won the 2006 Printz Award for his debut novel, Looking for Alaska.
46,Rick,Riordan,1964-06-05,NULL,American,An American author. He is known for writing the Percy Jackson & the Olympians series, about a demigod son of Poseidon.
47,Stephenie,Meyer,1973-12-24,NULL,American,An American author. She is best known for her Twilight series of novels.
48,E.B.,White,1899-07-11,1985-10-01,American,An American writer. He was the author of several highly popular books for children, including Stuart Little, Charlotte's Web, and The Trumpet of the Swan.
49,Roald,Dahl,1916-09-13,1990-11-23,British,A British novelist, short story writer, poet, and screenwriter. His books have sold more than 250 million copies worldwide.
50,Dr.,Seuss,1904-03-02,1991-09-24,American,An American children's author, political cartoonist, illustrator, poet, animator, and film producer. He is known for his more than 60 books.
